				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Chants/HGs (Question)<a name="37807"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 3 04 1:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yes, you can.
<br />

<br />
I'm 41st.  But I started chanting hill giants and ice giants at 39 and was able to solo yellows with ease.
<br />

<br />
I use Selo's Chain, Fufil's Chant, and Tuyen's Chant and equip my Trueborn Drum of Dark Rites.   First, I slow the mob then twist in the chants.  Pull him to an open area and circle him.   It's really easy.
<br />

<br />
The other day, I was Charm kiting frost giants-just two at a time.  Charm wore off and I went to recharm, but was out of mana (doh! forgot about mana) so I chant kited one down, then switched to the other.   Had a drakkel wolf join in and then hit him too.   I did have a sow potion for that though, on the other giants, I just used regular run speed because they were slowed.  
<br />

<br />
It's a slow kill, but unless you do something stupid, you won't ever be in any danger.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
